            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11827.xml">letter to Karl Höchberg, 13 January 1879</ref>. Höchberg’s colour theory may have been included in the article about music that he sent to CD (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9776.xml" resp="#automat" cert="low">Berg 1879</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">G. Allen 1879a. The quotation is from <hi rend="italic">Mind</hi> 4 (1879): 144.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2026.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Edmund Gurney’s</ref> article was ‘On discord’ (<hi rend="italic">Mind</hi> 4 (1879): 22–35), and was a response to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_81.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Grant Allen’s</ref> <hi rend="italic">Physiological aesthetics</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10100.xml" resp="#automat" cert="low">G. Allen 1877</ref>).</note>
